obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (67620)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Repealed.
  content `[Repealed by Act No. XIV of 1870.]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67620&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (67621)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Future Partitions to be made under provisions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67621&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `All partitions of estates which shall`
  line `be ordered to be made by the officers of Government after the passing of this Act, shall be made`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, whatever may be the tenure of the estate ordered to be divided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (67622)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `What Parties entitled to partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67622&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every recorded proprietor of a joint undivided estate`
  line `paving Revenue to Government, or of any portion thereof, whether such estate is held in common`
  line `tenancy or otherwise, is entitled to claim partition under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (67623)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Parties desirous of partition to apply to Collector in writing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67623&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `When any one or more of`
  line `the recorded proprietors of an estate, as described in the last preceding section, shall desire to have his`
  line `or their shares of the estate separated, in order that he or they may hold the same as a separate`
  line `property, or as separate properties, such proprietor or proprietors shall make a written application for`
  line `the purpose to the Collector of the District.`
  line
  line `Any two or more proprietors may apply to have their shares separated, and to hold the same as a`
  line `joint estate`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (67624)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Application to be signed, and certain particulars specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67624&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The application shall be signed`
  line `by the party or parties applying for the partition, and shall specify the nature of the tenure of the estate`
  line `sought to be divided.`
  line
  line `The names of all the co-sharers in the estate, the nature and extent of their respective shares so far`
  line `as the same may be known to the applicant or applicants, or can be ascertained by him or them, and`
  line `the mode of partition desired, shall also be stated.`
  line
  line `Otherwise may be rejected.--If the application does not contain the particulars above-mentioned,`
  line `the Collector may reject it.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (67625)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procedure of Collector on receipt of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67625&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Collector, on the receipt of an`
  line `application for partition, shall, if the application be in order, and not open to objection on the face of`
  line `it, publish a notification of the same at his office, and at some conspicuous place on the estate to`
  line `which the application relates, and shall invite any party in possession, who may not have joined in the`
  line `application, and who may object to the partition applied for, to appear before him either in person or by a duly constituted agent, on a day to be specified in the notification, not being less than fifteen, or`
  line `more than thirty days from the date of the notification, and state his objection.`
  line
  line `Notice to proprietors who have not joined therein.--If the application for partition shall not`
  line `have been made by all the recorded proprietors of the estate, notice of the application shall be served,`
  line `in the manner usual in the district for serving notices of the revenue officers, on such of the recorded`
  line `proprietors of the estate as shall not have joined in the application.`
  line
  line `Proclamation in case of service of notice being impracticable.--Provided that, if from any`
  line `cause such service cannot take place, a proclamation notifying such application shall be published, by`
  line `affixing it at the Mal - kachahri of such estate, or other conspicuous place thereon, or at the village`
  line `Chauri, Chaupal, or other conspicuous place in each village in such estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (67626)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `In case of valid objection being made within time allowed, application may be refused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67626&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If any objection be made to the partition, by any party in possession, within the time`
  line `allowed, and the Collector, on a consideration of such objection, be of opinion that there is any good`
  line `and sufficient reason, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, why the partition should be`
  line `absolutely disallowed, he may refuse the application, recording the grounds of his refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (67627)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Procedure if question of title, or of proprietary right, be raised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67627&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If the objection raise`
  line `any question of title, or of proprietary right, which shall not appear to have been already determined`
  line `by a Court of competent Jurisdiction, the Collector may either decline to grant the application until the`
  line `question in dispute shall have been determined by a competent Court, or he may proceed to inquire`
  line `into the merits of the objection.`
  line
  line `In the latter case the Collector, after making the necessary inquiry and taking such evidence as`
  line `may be adduced, shall record a proceeding declaring the nature and extent of the interests in the actual`
  line `possession of the party or parties applying for the partition, and any other party or parties who may be`
  line `affected thereby.`
  line
  line `Reference to arbitrators.--The procedure to be observed by the Collector in trying such cases`
  line `shall be that laid down in Act XIV of 1882 (to consolidate and amend the laws relating to the`
  line `procedure of the Courts of Civil Judicature) for the trial of original suits, and the Collector shall have`
  line `power to refer any question that may arise in such case to arbitration, and the provisions of`
  line `Chapter XXXVII (reference to arbitration) of the Code of Civil Procedure shall apply to so cases`
  line `referred by a Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (67628)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Decision of Collector equivalent to decision of civil Court, and open to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67628&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line All
  line `orders and decisions passed by the Collector under the last preceding Section, for declaring the rights`
  line `of parties, shall be held to be decisions of a Court of Civil Judicature of first instance, and shall be`
  line `open to appeal to the District or Sadr Court, according to the value of the claim, under the rules`
  line `applicable to regular appeals to those Courts.`
  line
  line `Appellate Court may, on appeal, stay partition.--Upon such appeal being made, the District or`
  line `Sadr Court, as the case may be, may issue a precept to the Collector, desiring him to stay the partition`
  line `pending the decision of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (67629)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Special appeal to Sadr Court..`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67629&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `From every decision passed under the last preceding section`
  line `by a District Court, a special appeal shall lie to the Sadr Court, under the rules for the time being in`
  line `force relating to special appeals to that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (67630)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Civil Court to entertain suits only on appeal from decision of Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67630&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `It shall not be`
  line `competent to the civil Court to entertain a suit, or application for the partition of an estate, except on`
  line `appeal from the decision of the Collector as herein before provided, anything contained in`
  line `Section 265 Act XIV of 1882 (to consolidate and amend the laws relating to the Procedure of the`
  line `Courts of Civil Judicature) to the contrary notwithstanding.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (67631)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Notification on partition being ordered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67631&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `When the Collector, after disposing of the`
  line `objections (if any) taken to the partition, shall order a partition to be made, he shall cause a`
  line `Notification to be published in his own Office, in the District Court, and at some conspicuous place on the estate which is to be divided, intimating his intention to proceed with the partition after thirty days`
  line `from the date of the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (67632)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Partition by whom carried out.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67632&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The partition shall be made by the Collector in whose`
  line `district the estate is situate, or, if the estate be situate in two or more districts, then by the Collector of`
  line `any one of such Districts, who may be specially ordered by the Commissioner of the Division, to`
  line `superintend the partition.`
  line
  line `If the estate be situated in two or more divisions, the partition shall be made by such Collector as`
  line `the Board of Revenue shall order.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (67633)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Assessment and levy of costs incurred in making partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67633&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The expense of making the`
  line `partition, and the allowances of the establishment necessary for the measurement and survey of the`
  line `lands, the preparation of papers, and any other charges, shall be fixed by the Collector.`
  line `The amount shall be paid under such rules as may from time to time be laid down by the Board of`
  line `Revenue with the sanction of the Local Government, and, in default of payment, may be realized`
  line `under the rules applicable to the recovery of arrears of rent or revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (67634)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Partition may be stayed, and proceedings quashed, by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67634&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `At any stage of`
  line `the proceedings after a partition shall have been ordered, if it shall appear from information which`
  line `was not before the Collector at the time the partition was ordered, or otherwise, that any reason not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act exists, why the partition should not be proceeded with, it`
  line `shall be competent to the Commissioner, on the report of the Collector, and subject to any orders that`
  line `the Board of Revenue may pass in the case, to stay the partition, and to order the proceedings to be`
  line quashed.
  line
  line `Decision not open to revision, by civil Court.--The decision of the Revenue authorities under`
  line `this Section shall not be open to revision by the civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (67635)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure after lapse of period mentioned in notification under section XII.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Repealed, so far as they relate to the North-Western Provinces, by Act XIX of 1873.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67635&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `After the`
  line `expiration of the period mentioned in the Notification referred to in Section XII of this Act, the`
  line `Collector shall, if necessary, cause a measurement of all the lands comprised in the estate to be made,`
  line `and a rent-roll of the same to be prepared.`
  line
  line `The village-papers which are required to be prepared and periodically deposited in the office of the`
  line `Collector, under the provisions of sections XI^1`
  line `and XII^1`
  line `, Regulation IX, 1833 (to modify certain`
  line `portions of Regulation VII, 1822, and Regulation IV, 1828; to provide for the more speedy and`
  line `satisfactory decision of Judicial Questions cognizable by Officers of Revenue employed in making`
  line `Settlements under the above Regulations; for enforcing the production of the village accounts; for the`
  line `more extensive employment of Native Agency in the Revenue Department; and to declare the intent of`
  line `Section V, Regulation VII, 1822, touching claims to Malikana), may be used for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `Provided that any of the proprietors shall be permitted to file a rent-roll of the estate, which shall`
  line `be accepted if acknowledged to be correct by all the proprietors.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (67636)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Examination of parties and their papers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67636&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may examine the parties on`
  line `solemn affirmation in regard to the papers produced before him, whether by the officer appointed to`
  line `make the partition, the proprietors, or otherwise.`
  line
  line `He shall also allow any shareholder to examine the papers so produced, and to take a copy of the`
  line `same, and after such examination he shall hear any objections which any of the shareholders may`
  line `make in respect to such papers.`
  line
  line `The Collector may direct any Deputy Collector or other officer subordinate to him to examine the`
  line `papers produced before him, and to make a report upon the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (67637)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Options of settlement by private agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67637&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Collector, on the completion of the enquiry allowed by the last preceding section, shall allow the parties the option of making a private partition of the estate and allotment of the public`
  line `revenue amongst themselves, within such time as he may fix, or, if the parties shall not consent to`
  line `make a private partition of the estate, or shall fail to make such partition within the time fixed by the`
  line `Collector, the Collector shall call upon them to state whether they are willing to refer the partition of`
  line `the estate, and the apportionment of the public revenue, to an arbitrator or arbitrators to be appointed`
  line `by them.`
  line
  line `The Collector may also offer the parties the option of referring any point arising in the course of a`
  line `partition to arbitration.`
  line
  line `The partition and allotment of the public revenue made by the parties, or by arbitrators appointed`
  line `by them, shall be subject to the confirmation of the Collector, and the orders of the superior`
  line Revenue-authorities.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (67638)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `If parties cannot agree as to arbitrators, latter may be appointed by Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67638&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `parties consent to refer the partition of the estate, and the allotment of the public Revenue, or any`
  line `point arising in the course of the partition, to arbitration, but they cannot agree amongst themselves as`
  line `to the arbitrator or arbitrators to be appointed, the Collector may appoint two or more persons to be`
  line `arbitrators in the case.`
  line
  line `In case of equality of votes, Collector to act as umpire.--If the arbitrators are equally divided`
  line `in opinion, the Collector shall act as umpire, and the partition made by the arbitrator or arbitrators`
  line `with whom the Collector shall concur, shall be the partition in the case.`
  line
  line `The same rule shall apply in respect of any point arising in the course of a partition, which shall`
  line `be referred to arbitration.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (67639)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appointment in place of arbitrator refusing, or being unable, to act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67639&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If any person, on`
  line `being appointed an arbitrator, shall refuse to act, or, after accepting the appointment, shall or become`
  line `incapable of acting, another person shall be appointed arbitrator in his stead, in the same manner in`
  line `which the first person was appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (67640)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Powers of Collector with regard to arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67640&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `After the arbitrators shall have`
  line `accepted the appointment, the Collector shall transmit the whole of the papers to them, and it shall be`
  line `competent to the Collector to exercise towards the arbitrators the same powers and authority for`
  line `securing their attendance, and the due completion of their award, which he is competent to exercise`
  line `towards witnesses summoned before him when acting judicially, for the purpose of compelling them`
  line `to attend and give evidence.`
  line
  line `The Collector shall also fix a time within which the arbitrator or arbitrators shall deliver the paper`
  line `of partition. On sufficient cause shown, the Collector may extend such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (67641)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Particulars to be specified in partition paper.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67641&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The arbitrators shall deliver a full and`
  line `complete paper of partition, specifying the separate estates into which they propose that the estate`
  line `shall be divided, the names of the parties to whom the several estates are proposed to be allotted, and`
  line `the amount of public Revenue to be assessed on each of such estates.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (67642)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Remuneration of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67642&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The arbitrators, on delivering the paper of partition as`
  line `aforesaid, shall be entitled to reasonable fees for their services, the amount to be fixed by the`
  line Collector.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (67643)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `In default of award by first arbitrators, partition may be referred to others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67643&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `paper of partition be not delivered within the time fixed by the Collector, or within any further period`
  line `to which the time may have been extended, the Collector may order that the partition shall be referred`
  line `to another arbitrator or arbitrators, to be chosen in the same manner and subject to the same rules as`
  line `the first.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (67677)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `In default of Private agreement, or settlement by arbitration, officer may be appointed to make partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67677&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `If the partition of the estate cannot be made by the parties`
  line `themselves, or by arbitration, under the foregoing rules, the Collector shall appoint an Officer to make the partition, and shall forward the whole of the papers to such Officer, and shall direct him to`
  line `proceed to the estate, and to make the partition within a time to be fixed by the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (67645)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Who shall summon proprietors by proclamation to attend proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67645&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Officer`
  line `appointed to make the partition shall issue a proclamation at the Mal-kachahari of the estate, or other`
  line `conspicuous place thereon, or at the village Chaunri, or Chaupal, requiring the several proprietors of`
  line `the estate to attend upon him in person, or by agent, during the time that the partition is being made.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (67678)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Estate may be attached and brought under khas management under superintendence of officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67678&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `At the commencement of the Revenue year current in the District, the`
  line `Collector may direct the Officer appointed to make the partition, or some other person, to attach the`
  line `estate, and to bring it under khas management under the personal superintendence of such Officer.`
  line
  line `The collections of the estate, after defraying the expenses of management, and any other expenses`
  line `with which the estate is chargeable, shall be applied to the payment of the Government Revenue, and`
  line `the residue shall be divided amongst the proprietors in proportion to their respective shares, at such`
  line `periods as the Collector may see fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (67647)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure in case of arrears of revenue accruing during course of partition of estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67647&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If an arrear of public Revenue shall accrue on an estate ordered to be divided, while the`
  line `partition of the estate is being made, any one or more of the proprietors may tender to the Collector`
  line `his or their quota of the balance, and the Collector shall receive the same, and credit the amount to the`
  line `share or shares of such proprietor or proprietors.`
  line
  line `If a sale of any part of the estate shall ultimately become necessary for the liquidation of any part`
  line `of such arrear which may remain due, only the share or shares of the proprietor or proprietors who`
  line `shall not have contributed their quota of the balance shall be sold in the first instance, and the partition`
  line `shall go on and be completed, in the same manner as if no arrear of public Revenue had accrued.`
  line
  line `The purchaser or purchasers of the share or shares sold shall be entitled to separate possession of`
  line `the estate or estates which, under the partition, would have been allotted to the defaulting proprietor or`
  line proprietors.
  line
  line `Provided always that, in all cases of a partition, the entire estate shall be considered responsible`
  line `for the public Revenue assessed upon it, until the partition shall have been completed, and the several`
  line `proprietors shall have been put into possession of the separate estates into which the estate may be`
  line `ordered to be divided, according as the same may be allotted to them.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (67648)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of officer charged with partition, in respect of measurement, &e .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67648&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `Officer appointed to make the partition shall consider it necessary, to assist him in making the same,`
  line `to cause a detailed measurement to be made of all the lands comprised in the estate, or a map of the`
  line `estate to be prepared, he shall exercise the same powers for making such measurement and map as are`
  line `vested in the Collector by any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (67649)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Division of lands held in common.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67649&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `When some of the lands forming the estate are held`
  line `in common, the Collector shall declare, by a proceeding to be held under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the principle and rule under which, in accordance with the village custom, such lands shall be divided;`
  line
  line `and he shall cause the partition of such lands to be made in conformity to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `The portion of the common land falling by such partition to the shares of the several co-sharers`
  line `shall be added to the lands held by them in severalty, and the several estates thus formed shall be`
  line `assessed and declared separate estates.`
  line
  line `Proviso.--Provided that it shall be in the discretion of the Collector to cause any transfer of lands,`
  line `agreed to by the parties, to be made previous to such declaration, and the new estate shall be declared`
  line `subject to the transfer so made.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (67650)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Collector may refuse to separate lands in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67650&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may refuse to`
  line `declare any lands held in severalty, and not liable to re-distribution according to special village`
  line `custom, a separate mehal, if the lands be so intermixed with other properties as to render the formation of a compact estate impossible, and if the parties affected by the partition decline to permit`
  line `of the transfers necessary for curing such defect.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (67651)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Where no lands held in common, lands in severalty may be declared separate estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67651&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Where there may be no lands held in common, the lands in severalty, held by the applicant`
  line `for partition, or assigned to him by the Collector under the provisions of this Act, shall be assessed`
  line `and declared a separate estate.`
  line
  line `Proviso as to transfer.--Provided that it shall be in the discretion of the Collector to cause any`
  line `transfer of lands, agreed to, or directed by his order, as provided in section XXX, to be made previous`
  line `to such declaration, and the new estate shall be declared subject to the transfer so made.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (67652)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Sharer failing to attend after proclamation, liable to forfeit right of objection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67652&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If any sharer, after the issue of the proclamation mentioned in Section XXVI of this Act,`
  line `shall fail to attend the Officer appointed to make the partition during the time the partition is being`
  line `made, no objection taken by such sharer to the partition shall be heard, unless such sharer can show`
  line `that his absence was not wilful, or unless for any good and sufficient reason it shall appear just and`
  line `proper to allow him to be heard against the partition.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (67653)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Partition may be stayed if parties so desire.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67653&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `If, at any time after an order shall have`
  line `been passed for making a partition, it shall appear, either from the report of the Officer appointed to`
  line `make the partition, or from any other information, that the parties are not desirous that the partition`
  line `should proceed, it shall be competent to the Collector, with the sanction of the Commissioner, to stop`
  line `the partition, and to strike the case off the file,`
  line
  line `Recovery of costs.--recovering from the sharers all costs and expenses incurred up to that time.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (67683)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Estates formed in course of partition to be as compact as possible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67683&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the`
  line `duty of the Officer appointed to make the partition, so far as circumstances will admit, to take care`
  line `that the estates into which the estate is divided shall consist of contiguous mehals or villages.`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the estate ordered to be divided shall not consist of a sufficient number of`
  line `villages to admit of one or more entire village or villages being included in each estate, the partition of`
  line `the village or villages of which the estate shall consist shall be made so as to render each estate as`
  line `compact as possible.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (67679)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Revenue to be assessed on each divided estate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67679&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The public Revenue shall be`
  line `assessed on each estate into which the property shall be ordered to be divided, in conformity to the`
  line `rules contained in any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (67680)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Circumstances to be considered in making partition`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67680&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `In selecting the villages or`
  line
  line `lands to be included in each separate estate,`
  line
  line `the advantages or disadvantages arising from situation;`
  line
  line `the vicinity of roads, railways, navigable rivers, or canals;`
  line
  line `the nature and quality of the soil and produce;`
  line
  line `the quantity of culturable and unculturable waste land;`
  line
  line `the depth at which water may be procurable;`
  line
  line `the number of tanks and wells;`
  line
  line `the state of the embankments and water-courses; and`
  line
  line `any other local circumstances affecting the present, or likely to influence the future, value of the`
  line `lands, shall be duly considered:`
  line
  line `and the villages or lands to be included in each estate shall be fairly and impartially selected.`
  line
  line `So far as may be practicable, and consistent with compactness of partition, lands held in severalty`
  line `shall be left in the possession of the parties holding the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (67681)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Rule when dwelling house belonging to one sharer, is situate on ground to be allotted to Another sharer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67681&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `If a dwelling-house belonging to one sharer shall be situate on any`
  line `land, or in any village, which it may be necessary to include in the share of another sharer, the`
  line `proprietor of such house shall be at liberty to retain it, with the offices, buildings, and grounds,`
  line `immediately attached thereto, upon agreeing to pay to the proprietor of the land or village in which`
  line `the same is situate an equitable rent for the ground.`
  line
  line `The limits of the ground and the rent to be paid for it shall be fixed by the Officer making the`
  line `partition, and shall be stated in the paper of partition`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (67657)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Rule as to tanks, wells, water-courses, and embankments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67657&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Tanks, wells,`
  line `water-courses, and embankments, shall be considered as attached to the land for the benefit of which`
  line `they were originally made.`
  line
  line `In cases in which, from the extent, situation, or construction of such works, it shall be found`
  line `necessary to continue them the joint property of the proprietors of two or more of the estates into`
  line `which the estate may be divided, the paper of partition shall specify, as far as circumstances may`
  line `admit, the extent to which the proprietors of each of such estates may make use of the same, and the`
  line `proportion of the charges for repairs to be borne by them respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (67658)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Rule as to places of worship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67658&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Places of worship, which shall have been held in common`
  line `previous to the partition of an estate, shall continue to be so held, unless the parties shall otherwise`
  line `agree amongst themselves, in which case they shall state in writing the agreement into which they`
  line `have entered, and the Officer making the partition shall enter a note of the agreement in the paper of`
  line partition.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (67682)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Particulars to be contained in paper of partition to be submitted by officer making same.Map to be also submitted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67682&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `When the Officer appointed to make the partition shall have completed the partition, and`
  line `allotted the public Revenue on each of the estates into which it is proposed that the estate shall be`
  line `divided, he shall prepare and submit to the Collector a paper of partition, showing how he proposes to`
  line `divide the estate, and to apportion the public Revenue.`
  line
  line `This paper shall specify`
  line `the names of the Mehals or villages included in each separate estate;`
  line
  line `the gross produce of each Mehal and village for the three years immediately preceding the year in`
  line `which the partition is ordered to be made;`
  line
  line `the names of the parties to whom the several estates are allotted, and the proportion of the public`
  line `Revenue proposed to be assessed on each of such estates, with any remarks regarding the mode`
  line `observed in selecting the lands included in each estate, and the accounts upon which the`
  line `apportionment of the public Revenue assessed thereon shall have been based, as may be necessary for`
  line `the information of the Collector.`
  line
  line `The paper shall further contain a detail of the adjustments, if any, which shall have been made in`
  line `respect to any tanks, places of worship, or other matters, as specified in the preceding Sections.`
  line
  line `Map to be also submitted.--The Officer appointed to make the partition shall also submit a map,`
  line `showing the several estates into which the estate is proposed to be divided.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (67660)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Procedure of Collector thereupon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67660&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Collector shall take into consideration the`
  line `partition proposed by the Officer appointed to make the partition, and, after calling for any further`
  line `information which he shall deem necessary, and disposing of any objections which shall be taken to`
  line `the partition, and allotment of public Revenue, as proposed by such Officer, he shall submit a report`
  line `to the Commissioner, together with such of the papers of the case as shall appear to him essential.`
  line
  line `He shall also forward a list of the papers not sent.`
  line
  line `The Collector shall record his opinion whether the proposed partition should be confirmed or`
  line `modified, and in the latter case, he shall state the nature of the modification which, in his opinion,`
  line `should be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (67684)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Commissioner may confirm or modify partition, subject to appeal to Board of Revenue ; andmay direct division by lot, under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67684&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall either uphold the partition proposed by the Collector, or modify`
  line `the same. The decision of the Commissioner shall not be open to revision by the Civil Court, but shall`
  line `be subject to appeal to the Board of Revenue.`
  line
  line `The Commissioner, before coming to a decision, may call for any additional papers, or direct any`
  line `further inquiry that he shall consider necessary.`
  line
  line `And may direct division by lot under certain circumstances.--He may also, if he think proper,`
  line `direct that, when two or more of the estates into which it is proposed to divide the estate shall consist`
  line `of the same proportions of the entire estate, the parties entitled thereto shall draw lots for the same`
  line `before the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (67685)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Procedure by Collector on receipt of order of Commissioner, or of Board of Revenue on appeal`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67685&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `On the receipt of the order of the Commissioner or if an appeal be preferred to the Board`
  line `of Revenue, then, of the order passed on the appeal, the Collector shall cause the same to be published`
  line `in his Office, and in some conspicuous place in each of the estates separately constituted by such`
  line order.
  line
  line `The Collector shall at the same time specify the date from which each of the estates shall be held`
  line `to be a separate estate, and shall enter the several estates into which the estate has been divided in the`
  line `Register of Estates paying Revenue to Government.`
  line
  line `The Collector shall give the several proprietors possession of the estates allotted to them, and, if`
  line `necessary, may avail himself of the assistance of the Magistrate in giving possession.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (67686)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Government may order new allotment of public revenue among estates formed by partition, in case of fraud or error in original allotment being proved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67686&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `In order to prevent`
  line `collusion or error in the distribution of the public Revenue assessed upon an estate which may ordered`
  line `to be divided into two or more distinct estates, if it shall be proved to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Government, within twelve years from and after the date of confirmation of the partition, that the`
  line `public Revenue was fraudulently or erroneously apportioned at the time of the partition, the`
  line `Government shall have power to order a new allotment of the public Revenue upon the several estates`
  line `into which such estate may have been divided, conformably to the principles prescribed in this Act, on`
  line `an estimate of the gross produce of each estate at the time of the partition, to be made agreeably to the`
  line `best evidence and information which may be procurable respecting the same.`
  line
  line `Such order shall not be liable to be contested in the Civil Court.`
  line
  line `The parties whose estates may be declared to have been under-assessed shall be-required to pay to`
  line `the proprietors of the estates which shall have been over-assessed, the sum in which they shall be`
  line `found to have been over-assessed, and in default of payment, the amount shall be leviable by the`
  line `process prescribed for the recovery of arrears of rent or Revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (67687)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Consequence to party having interest in estate, if he neglect to affirm or establish such interest while estate under attachment with a view to partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67687&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `If, during the time an`
  line `estate is under attachment with a view to the partition of the same, any party shall neglect or omit to`
  line `claim, by a suit, any right or title he may then have to the ownership or occupancy, at a fixed rent, of`
  line `any land situated in such estate, or any other interest therein, such, neglect or omission shall be a valid`
  line `plea in bar of any suit relating to such right, title, or interest, unless the party can satisfy the Court that`
  line `there was good and sufficient reason for his neglect or omission to institute the suit at or before such`
  line time.
  line
  line `Provided that this Section shall not bar any action for arrears of rent, or the enhancement or`
  line `alteration of rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (67688)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Holder of decree of civil Court, awarding right to portion of estate, may apply for partition, and Collector may proceed thereon under Act`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67688&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any Court of Civil`
  line `Judicature shall pass a decree, awarding to any person the proprietary right in a portion of an estate`
  line `paying Revenue to Government, whether the portion so awarded shall consist of a fractional share in the whole, or a part, of the estate, or of specific lands, the decree-holder may apply to the Collector for`
  line `a partition of the estate;`
  line
  line `and on the receipt of such application, the Collector shall proceed thereupon under the provisions`
  line `of this Act, which are hereby declared applicable to such applications.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (67666)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Union in certain cases of severed portions of estates originally undivided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67666&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `If two or`
  line `more estates, which may have originally formed portions of the same estate, shall come into the`
  line `possession of one person, such person shall be entitled to have such estates united, and to hold them`
  line `as a single estate;`
  line
  line `or if two or more persons shall have separate possession of their respective shares of an estate`
  line `which was originally held as a joint undivided estate, such persons may apply to have their shares`
  line `united, and to hold them as one estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (67667)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Application for such union how made, and how dealt with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67667&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line The
  line `applications for the union of the estates, or of the shares of the estate, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `made in writing to the Collector of the District in which the estates, or shares of the estate, are situate,`
  line `and the Collector (provided he see no objection) shall comply with the application, and cause the`
  line `necessary entries to be made in the records of his Office, reporting the case to the superior Revenue`
  line Authorities.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (67689)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title Repealed.
  content `[Repealed by Act No. XIV of 1870.]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67689&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (67690)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Provisions of Act applied to partition of estates held free from payment of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67690&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act may, in so far as the same are applicable be applied, by order`
  line `of the Local Government to the partition of any estate held free from the payment of Government`
  line Revenue.
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (67669)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Control of Collector’s proceedings under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67669&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `In the performance of his duties under this`
  line `Act, the Collector shall be subject to the general direction and control of the Commissioner of the`
  line `Division, and the Board of Revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (67670)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Orders of Collector when open to revision by superior Revenue-authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67670&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `All orders passed by a Collector under this Act, unless otherwise provided, not being`
  line `orders or decisions within the meaning of Section IX, shall be open to revision by the superior`
  line `Revenue Authorities.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (67671)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `What other officers may exercise power vested in Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67671&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The powers`
  line `vested in a Collector by this Act may be exercised by a Deputy Collector, or other Officer, vested`
  line `with the full powers of a Collector, subject to the control of the Collector of the District.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (67672)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to be exercised by Collector, or officer appointed to make partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67672&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `In carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act, the Collector shall exercise the powers described in Regulation II, 1819,`
  line `Regulation VII, 1822, and Regulations IX and XIV, 1825.`
  line
  line `Any Officer appointed to make a partition under this Act may also exercise the powers described`
  line `in the foregoing Regulations, so far as the same may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (67673)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of officers exercising jurisdiction under Act, with regard to false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67673&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If, in any case in which a Collector or other Officer shall exercise Jurisdiction under this`
  line `Act, any person is guilty of the offence of giving or fabricating false evidence, or of forgery, as`
  line `defined in the Indian Penal Code, or of abetting any of those offences, such Collector or other Officer`
  line `shall have the same powers in respect of such offence, and of the person charged with, committing the`
  line `same, as are vested by the Code of Criminal Procedure in a Civil Court, when any such offence is`
  line `committed before or against such Court, or when a document charged to be a forgery is given in`
  line `evidence in any proceedings in such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (67674)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Board of Revenue to be guided by instruction of Local Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67674&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `In the execution`
  line `of the duties vested in the Board of Revenue by this Act, the Board shall be guided by such orders or`
  line `instructions as they may from time to time receive from the Local Government, to whom they shall`
  line `apply in all cases which shall appear to the Board not to have been provided for by the existing law.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (67675)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67675&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Unless there be something in the subject or context repugnant to such`
  line `construction, words importing the singular number shall include the plural number, and words`
  line `importing the plural number shall include the singular number; and`
  line
  line `words importing the masculine gender shall include females.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (67676)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Territorial scope of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903&sectionId=67676&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00078_186319_1659335140903
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall extend only to such parts of the North-Western`
  line `Provinces of the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal as are subject to the general Regulations of that`
  line `Presidency; but the Act may be extended, by order of the Local Government, either wholly or in part,`
  line `to any Non-Regulation Province under such Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
